verbose_text: No mineralisation was observed in the absence of beta-glycerophosphate; normal, selective mineralisation of the collagenous matrix occurred in the presence of 2-5 mM beta-glycerophosphate, whereas 10 mM beta-glycerophosphate caused non specific, dystrophic mineralisation and a significant inhibition of TNAP staining (XREF_FIG).
evidence: beta-glycerophosphate caused non-specific, dystrophic mineralisation and a significant inhibition of TNAP
